The article discusses President Obama's participation in the 2012 National Level Exercise (NLE), which is sponsored by FEMA to test the country's ability to respond to and recover from catastrophic events. The focus of this exercise was on managing a cyber incident that affects critical infrastructure. The President held a Cabinet meeting to discuss the decisions that would need to be made in such a situation. The article highlights the importance of protecting critical infrastructure from cyber intrusions and mentions that the Administration has proposed legislation to ensure their security. The Senate is currently considering this legislation. The article emphasizes the need for Congress to pass legislation to protect the nation from cyber threats while safeguarding privacy and civil liberties.